Resolve providing for the study and investigation relative to expanding the in-state higher
education tuition and fee waiver program.
1 Resolved, that a special commission is hereby established for the purposes of making an
2 investigation and study relative to expanding the eligibility of the tuition and fee waiver program
3 established in section 19 of chapter 15A of the General Laws to clients of state programs
4 inclusive but not limited to the departments comprised of the members of the special
5 commission.
6 The Commission shall consist of the following members or their designees:
7 the Chair of the Board of Higher Education, who will serve as chair;
8 the Secretary of the Executive Office of Health and Human Services;
9 the Secretary of the Executive Office of Housing and Livable Communities;
10 the Commissioner of the Department of Developmental Services;
11 the Commissioner of the Department of Mental Health;
1 of 2

12 the Commissioner of the Commission for the Deaf and Hard of Hearing;
13 the Commissioner Massachusetts Commission for the Blind;
14 the Commissioner of the Department of Transitional Assistance;
15 the Commissioner of MassAbility.
16 The Commission shall: (i) identify programs with clients inclusive but not limited to the
17 departments of which the special commission is comprised who should be made eligible for the
18 tuition and fee waiver program established in section 19 of chapter 15A of the General Laws; (ii)
19 compile data concerning the number and cost of new clients identified by the commission to
20 become eligible for the tuition and fee waiver and; (iii) identify possible sources of funding for
21 the expanded tuition and fee waiver program.
22 All appointments shall be made not later than 30 days after the effective date of this
23 resolve.
24 The Commission shall submit its findings and recommendations for legislation to the
25 Clerks of the Senate and the House of Representatives no later than January 1st, 2027.
